game (
	name "Zero no Tsukaima - Shou-akuma to Harukaze no Concerto (Japan)"
	serial "SLPS-25709"
	description "The Familiar of Zero (Zero no Tsukaima) is a fantasy and comedy-oriented series of Japanese light novels written by Noboru Yamaguchi, with illustrations by Eiji Usatsuka. Media Factory published 20 volumes between June 2004 and February 2011. The series was left unfinished due to the author's death on April 4, 2013.[2] The story features several characters from the second year class of a magic academy in a fictional magical world with the main characters being the inept mage Louise and her familiar from Earth, Saito Hiraga."
	developer "Marvelous"
	publisher "Marvelous"
	releaseyear "2007"
