game (
	name "Scooby-Doo - Mystery Mayhem (Europe)"
	serial "SLES-51883"
	description "The sequel to 2002's Night of 100 Frights on PlayStation 2, Scooby-Doo: Mystery Mayhem has the paranormal-probing pooch and his mystery-loving friends on another case involving ghosts, monsters, and scheming humans. Players alternate control between Scooby and Shaggy to locate a powerful book called the Tome of Doom, which a wealthy businessman is using to summon a ghastly assortment of creatures. Like its predecessor, the game is played from a third-person viewpoint set behind either Scooby or Shaggy, who each offer different abilities."
